law.text:
The effectiveness of efforts to protect children removed from their homes from abuse and neglect shall be measured by:
the incidence of indicated or unsubstantiated findings of child abuse or neglect of children in the custody of a local department, or a placement agency, for placements:
in foster care homes;
in kinship care homes;
in residential treatment centers or group homes;
with family members; and
in other forms of substitute care;
the incidence of indicated or unsubstantiated findings of child abuse or neglect within 12 months following the release of the child committed to the Department; and
any other indicators adopted by the Secretary under § 5-1302 of this subtitle.
